##Don't forget the old people who live alone in Wuhan

Micro Signal Zhenshigushi1

Feature description, a true story every day that touches the heart of the original.

After the closure of Wuhan, the life of the old people living alone is facing great risks. A group of young people organized to help the community to help the elderly living alone with incomplete or mobility, free food delivery support. For more than a month, volunteers approached the world of 1,500 elderly people living alone to consolidate their daily lives.

The following is an oral account by Zhou Wei (not his real name) , founder of the Volunteer Program "looking for elderly people living alone" :

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After the closure of Wuhan, the life of the old people living alone is facing great risks. A group of young people organized to help the community to help the elderly living alone with incomplete or mobility, free food delivery support. For more than a month, volunteers approached the world of 1,500 elderly people living alone to consolidate their daily lives.

The following is an oral account by Zhou Wei (not his real name) , founder of the Volunteer Program "looking for elderly people living alone" :

Year: 2020

Location: Wuhan

Year: 2020

Location: Wuhan

We're a temporary volunteer group for the outbreak, just a dozen people. Until mid-february, our primary focus was on the admission of patients with NCP, followed by an online free clinic for non-pneumonia patients. It is in this process that attention is paid to the needs of elderly people living alone.

We had elderly patients who were critically ill or had a stroke, who were in very poor health, and some of the chronically ill were at risk of drug withdrawal. "The old man at home has no food to eat. " "What if the old man has no medicine? " Such a plea for help was mixed in with thousands of private messages on Weibo.

On the night of February 10th, a woman contacted us. Her parents live in Nanhu, Wuhan. Her father, who suffers from Parkinson and diabetes, is unable to take care of himself, has been off his medication for many days and can't sleep at night. Mother did not trust to leave father alone at home, unable to go to the hospital to prescribe drugs. She's out of town. She's in a hurry.

Strict control at that time, individual community can not go in and out, drug delivery volunteers every night after seven o'clock, while the community on duty staff shift, can sneak out, ride to the three towns in Wuhan drug delivery. That night, volunteers to the Provincial People's Hospital Emergency Department for the elderly to buy medicine, but the doctor said during the day in outpatient medicine can be prescribed. The next day, the volunteers went to the clinic early in the morning to line up, bought all the medicine immediately sent to the elderly. Later, the woman told us that my father was finally able to sleep at night.

Most of our children care about the elderly, but we have also experienced situations where we simply walk away because of distance. An elderly woman was admitted to the hospital with a suspected infection and her son took her to the hospital. There were not enough beds in the hospital. He left a quilt and some food for the old man and left. Back home, crazy to call volunteers, volunteers to help watch, it is very chilling.

In addition to these critical situations, the average age of the elderly people we encounter living alone is over 70, mobility is disabled, and most do not use mobile shopping. Once the lack of food, lack of medicine, can only tough, or from time to time by the neighbors to help. So as soon as we see a request for help from an elderly person, we verify it and help.

After Hubei Province "should receive receive, should treat thoroughly" order issued, most of the new crown pneumonia patients were admitted gradually, we have set aside special time for the elderly living alone to deliver vegetables, medicine. On February 21, I posted a post: If you have elderly people living alone or disabled people in your home in Wuhan who are not convenient to buy food, you can contact the community to deliver food to your home. If the community does not give food to me, you can give me feedback, and we will communicate with the community.

We need to get the word out that we can help, and I've found that we can't do it alone. I happen to know the head of the A2N (Anti-2019-ncov) epidemic volunteer group, who are online volunteers from all over the country, whose main job is to spread science and dispel rumors. We decided to play to their strengths, A2N integration of online resources, gathering information on elderly people living alone. And we deal with the community more, can further verify and offline delivery.

On February 26, four volunteers from A2n joined the campaign and posted a poster in various channels, "looking for elderly people living alone who can't get food (Wuhan only) . ". As of March 5, A2n had received nearly 1,500 requests for help through various channels, most of them from relatives of elderly people.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Looking for old people living alone poster

When we check information, we ask if we've tried online shopping, takeout errands. If the elderly person is not able to walk down the stairs to get food, has he sought help from the community. We started offline support when the community was understaffed. This is by far the most efficient way to fill a gap. There are probably only a few dozen elderly people who actually need us to deliver food to them.

Every night, we would plan in advance to the next day to deliver vegetables, and the boss of the food, let him leave us vegetables, preferably stored for a long time cabbage, radish and other vegetables. The quota for each family is about 200 yuan. If you need to buy oil, it's a little more expensive.

From the first line of volunteer feedback, I saw the living conditions of elderly people living alone. Although the elderly lack of food, but the overall state of mind are still good, very optimistic. I was most impressed by the A2N volunteers small fish follow-up Grandma Xie.

On the evening of February 28, Granny Xie, 77, added Xiaoyu's Wechat to our poster. The first sentence grandma Xie sent was: "Thank you for your efforts and hard work. "

Xie, who had no children, lived alone for 15 years after her husband died. Living alone, she took good care of themselves, usually like to practice at home writing brush, do clothes.

Because can not buy a mask, Wuhan after the closure of the city, grandma Xie never went downstairs, bought food before the New Year had already eaten up. So a small bowl of Pumpkin Porridge, with a dish of fermented bean curd and Tamarind, eat twice a day like this. Xie said she was a light eater. "If you eat a little, you can live. "

Before the outbreak, grandma Xie and neighbors eat, specially put on a big red cotton-padded Jacket, sat on the Sofa to take a photo. Later, she wrote on the photo: "to stay at home is to contribute to society. ". She told fish, not afraid of what happened to them, but if infected with the virus, do not know how many people to trouble.

Xie also worried that she was disturbing the volunteers, repeatedly stressed: If convenient, to help her take some food, she ate a little cheap food on her own enough, if busy do not worry about her.

After we recorded grandma Xie's condition, we ordered takeout for her the next day. While waiting for delivery boy, Small Fish Accompany Xie Grandma to talk, she told small fish, never so timely reply her message: "You are willing to chat with the Old Lady, do not dislike, you are good! "

Xie Grandma wearing the only mask to get food, small fish told her to change clothes, with alcohol sterilization bag of vegetables, mask do not use. These small concern, let thanks grandma regrets, once those she helped, but also to a special period of strangers met by chance.

In recent days, Xie Grandma also to fish voice singing, fish and Xie grandma to share photos, about the epidemic after the past to see her. In fact, the elderly living alone is not lack of food, but from the emotional concern. A psychological lack of support, that's their real dilemma.

On March 6, I got a call from an old woman I had helped, and she said she needed a few more medications. I couldn't hear her clearly, so I asked my doctor friend to contact my grandmother. After doctor friend communicates, discover grandma is not short of medicine and dish, contact us however all the time. Instead, we found a professional therapist for grandma.

Our small group, perhaps the most unorganized of all volunteer organizations, is the one that doesn't have a plan. We don't have a goal. How many people do we want to help. One person asks for help, one person asks for help. If 1,000 people ask for help, we'll help 1,000. The demand has increased. We'll have more men.

Our original intention was to actually help elderly people living alone on the edge, but we still heard some voices of doubt.

At first, as long as the old man's request is reasonable, we will try our best to satisfy it. Now, because only two volunteers have a community pass, it is inevitable that there is a lack of care. On February 29th, an old man called us and asked why she didn't get what she needed. He said he was watching TV and would give fruit if he wanted to volunteer.

Previously, I collected information about people seeking help on Weibo, mainly elderly people who have lost their only child, children who lost their parents during the epidemic, and disabled people who are unable to live easily. Some commented, "why do you collect information from others, who authorized you? You just take other people's information to deceive people. " Others said, your micro-blog at least to verify. To make people trust us a little bit more, I actually went and added V to Weibo.

I was angry and worried that some people would have given up on asking for help if they saw it. My friend comforted me: "because if a person really desperate, ID number can be given to you, if there is no life, personal privacy has no meaning at all. ". People who really need help will do whatever it takes to hold on."

We deliver food and medicine to the old people for free. The volunteer does not have the approval of the Civil Affairs Department, does not have the fund-raising qualification. In addition to buying food for the elderly, other items (such as donating protective items to patients'families) have already cost tens of thousands of dollars. Recently, I've been providing legal advice through paid questions and answers on Weibo, using my legal earnings to continue helping those in need.

According to our verification and observation on the front line, at present, the proportion of elderly people who have no food to eat is very small, and in most cases it is still information block. There may still be some old people living alone that have been left out, and we'll keep looking, even if it's like looking for a needle in a haystack.

This period of time, I saw a lot of people who died because of the epidemic, want to stand out to help everyone, is also to find a ray of comfort for themselves.

- END -

By Cheng Kun
